##Offensive Defense in Cyber Security

#Offensive Security
*'To defend from an attacker, one must think like an Attacker!'*
For one to defend from bad actors(hackers) one must also act like one, by breaking into systems(hardware and software) and networks by, exploiting vulnerabilities, 
sofware holes/bugs(like, day 1 pataches aka zero day attacks or by sloppy or bad code), finding loops holes into systems/networks and gaining unauthorised access by,
escalating privileges in the system/networks of an organisation. 

#Roles
- 🤼 Red Teaming(Red Teamer), they act like a Hacker(Bad actor/threat actors) and attack the organisations systems/networks, finding attack vectors, using attack methods,
      breaking into applications and finding loop holes in to systems/networks. They then write detailed reports about how,what,when and where they attacked and what 
      vulnerabilities and risks they found like, the use of social engineering through phishing emails(tricking a person/employee by sending an email that looks official) and 
      Social media phishing(going through social media and pretending to know the employee(s)). Or simply from Zero day attacks, vulnerabilities in new software/applications
      that had just been released or even by, finding existing vulnerbailities in preexisting systems/networks.
